# Direct-push path: where the "Push to KunthiveOS DB" button writes leads.
# You only need ONE of these — and usually NEITHER, because the scraper will
# auto-read ../KunthiveOS/.db-conn.json (the sibling repo's local creds).
#
# Override only if your KunthiveOS checkout lives elsewhere:

# 1. A full Postgres URL (Supabase: Project Settings → Database → Connection string)
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:PASSWORD@db.xxxx.supabase.co:5432/postgres?sslmode=require

# 2. Or point at a .db-conn.json by path:
# KUNTHIVE_OS_DB_CONN=/Users/you/Documents/Beta/KunthiveOS/.db-conn.json
